# Coding Standards and Best Practices

## HTML Standards
1. Use semantic HTML5 elements
2. Maintain proper document structure with DOCTYPE and meta tags
3. Include proper Korean language support:
   ```html
   <html lang="ko">
   <meta charset="UTF-8">
   ```

## CSS Standards
1. Use BEM naming convention for CSS classes
2. Implement mobile-first responsive design
3. Maintain consistent color scheme:
   - Primary colors from university branding
   - Secondary colors for UI elements
   - Accessible contrast ratios

## JavaScript Standards
1. Use modern ES6+ features
2. Implement proper error handling
3. Follow modular code organization
4. Include comments for complex logic

## Accessibility Requirements
1. Maintain WCAG 2.1 compliance
2. Include proper ARIA labels
3. Ensure keyboard navigation support
4. Provide alt text for all images

## Performance Guidelines
1. Optimize image assets
2. Minimize HTTP requests
3. Implement lazy loading for images
4. Use proper caching strategies

## Browser Support
- Chrome (latest 2 versions)
- Firefox (latest 2 versions)
- Safari (latest 2 versions)
- Edge (latest 2 versions)

## Code Organization
- Keep related files together
- Use meaningful file names
- Maintain consistent file structure
- Document complex functions and components
